topic.title: Multi-Configuration Command

body.p: The Multi-Configuration Command is to get configuration file information for Multi-configuration partition.
This command has the following Sub-Commands:

ol.li: 0x0 – Check if current configuration partition supports Multi-configuration feature or not;
0x1 - Get the file number in configuration partition;
0x2 – Get configuration file index currently used;
0x3 – Get the start address of the configuration file specified
0x4 - Get the length of the configuration file specified

table.title: MRPC Multi-Configuration Command Return Value Values

entry.p: Current configuration partition does not support Multi multi-configuration feature
